The bug in the program is that it only updates `lastApproved` when an event
event is not `approved: true`, but we want to update it regardless of wheth
whether or not the event is `approved: false`. So the condition to break th
the loop should be changed from `if !event.approved` to `if event.approved 
== true`.

Here's the corrected program:

```tundra
val events = [
  { id: "A", approved: true },
  { id: "B", approved: true },
  { id: "C", approved: false }
];

var lastApproved = "none";
for (event in events) {
  if (event.approved == true) {
    lastApproved = event.id;
  }
}

print(lastApproved);
```
This program will iterate over all the events and update `lastApproved` whe
whenever it encounters an approved event, regardless of whether or not othe
other non-approved events follow. The result should be "B".
